  "text": "\u2022 Adaptation in a macro-evolutionary fitness seascape (c 1, 0 < \u03c5 \u03c5): The divergencediversity ratio takes the form \u2126(\u03c4 |c, \u03c5) = \u2126(\u03c4 |c, \u03c5 = 0) + \u2126 ad (\u03c4 |\u03c5), with \u2126 ad (\u03c4 |\u03c5) = (\u03c5/\u03c5)(\u00b5\u03c4 ) [1 + O(\u03c5\u03c4 )]. This form displays two macro-evolutionary regimes: the driftdominated regime for \u03c4 \u2126 stab /\u00b5 and the adaptive regime for \u03c4 \u2126 stab /\u00b5. In the latter regime, the ratio of the two \u2126 components is related to the cumulative fitness flux [CITATION_1] , \u2126 ad (\u03c4 ) \u2126 stab \u2248 \u03c5c\u03c4 = 2N \u03a6(\u03c4 ) .",
